response: Take cues from your body for drinking water. The first cue will be parched lips. When you feel thirsty, your lips dry. Drink water immediately when this happens. Another indicator is your urine. Your urine should be clear. If it is yellow in color or darker, you should understand that your body is dehydrated and you need to drink more water. Do you want to know more?
